<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Watchdog on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/watchdog/</link><description>Recent content in Watchdog on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/watchdog/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] BSOD DPC_WATCHDOG_VIOLATION iaStorA.sys Intel RST Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/bsod-dpc-watchdog-iastora/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/bsod-dpc-watchdog-iastora/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-bsod-dpc_watchdog_violation-iastorasys-intel-rst-fix"&gt;[Solution] BSOD DPC_WATCHDOG_VIOLATION iaStorA.sys Intel RST Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DPC_WATCHDOG_VIOLATION with &lt;code&gt;iaStorA.sys&lt;/code&gt; is a Blue Screen error caused by the Intel Rapid Storage Technology (RST) driver taking too long to complete a deferred procedure call. The watchdog timer detects the hang and crashes the system to prevent data corruption.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error is extremely common on laptops and desktops with Intel chipsets, especially after Windows updates or when the Intel RST driver is outdated.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] BSOD DPC_WATCHDOG_VIOLATION storahci.sys Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/bsod-dpc-watchdog-storahci/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/windows/bsod-dpc-watchdog-storahci/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-bsod-dpc_watchdog_violation-storahcisys-fix"&gt;[Solution] BSOD DPC_WATCHDOG_VIOLATION storahci.sys Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DPC_WATCHDOG_VIOLATION with &lt;code&gt;storahci.sys&lt;/code&gt; is a Blue Screen error caused by the Standard AHCI (Advanced Host Controller Interface) storage driver taking too long to complete a deferred procedure call. The watchdog timer detects the hang and crashes the system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error is common on systems using the standard Windows AHCI driver for SATA storage controllers, especially after Windows updates or when storage hardware is failing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The full blue screen message reads:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Systemd Startup Timeout Exceeded</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/timeout-start/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/timeout-start/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="systemd-startup-timeout-exceeded"&gt;Systemd Startup Timeout Exceeded&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Systemd kills the service process when it fails to signal readiness or complete startup within the configured timeout. The default &lt;code&gt;TimeoutStartSec&lt;/code&gt; is 90 seconds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The service takes longer than the configured &lt;code&gt;TimeoutStartSec&lt;/code&gt; to start&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The service does not properly signal readiness via &lt;code&gt;Type=notify&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;ExecStartPost&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The service is blocked on a resource (disk, network, database)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A blocking dependency is stalling the startup sequence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="increase-the-start-timeout"&gt;Increase the Start Timeout&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ini" data-lang="ini"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Service]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;TimeoutStartSec&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;300&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="set-timeout-to-infinity-use-sparingly"&gt;Set Timeout to Infinity (Use Sparingly)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ini" data-lang="ini"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Service]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;TimeoutStartSec&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;infinity&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-notify-type-for-long-starting-services"&gt;Use Notify Type for Long-Starting Services&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ini" data-lang="ini"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;[Service]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Type&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;notify&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ExecStart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;/usr/bin/my-app --daemon&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;WatchdogSec&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;30&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="diagnose-what-is-blocking-startup"&gt;Diagnose What Is Blocking Startup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;journalctl -u &amp;lt;service-name&amp;gt; -n &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100&lt;/span&gt; --no-pager
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;systemd-analyze blame
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;systemd-analyze critical-chain &amp;lt;service-name&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="add-watchdog-support"&gt;Add Watchdog Support&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// In your application code, send READY=1 when ready
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sd_notify&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;READY=1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Service exceeded 90s startup timeout&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# my-app.service: Startup operation timed out, killing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: set TimeoutStartSec=300 in unit file&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Service waiting on database that takes long to initialize&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# my-app.service: Timed out starting&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: add After=postgresql.service and increase TimeoutStartSec&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/service-failed/"&gt;Service Failed&lt;/a&gt; — process exited with error code&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/systemd/failed-dependency/"&gt;Failed Dependency&lt;/a&gt; — dependency service failed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>